The defendant Shanona R Davis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court performs plea colloquy and finds defendant guilty of count #3.  Penalty enhancer is dismissed. State gives sentencing recommendations. Atty Buttery Williams makes statements regarding sentencing. Defendant makes Statements. Defendant is sentenced to the following:

COUNT #3:

IMPOSED 

JAIL: 17 DAYS (CREDIT FOR TIME SERVED)

COSTS:  $243.00 + $250.00 DNA surcharge, to be paid at $25.00/month commencing on 05/01/16, alternate is 4 days jail. 

Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
